poptosis by the release of a soluble, active form of TRAIL. In our model, Fas ligand (CD95L) appears to play a limited role in lyssavirus-mediated neuroblastoma cell death. Similarly, tumor necrosis factor alpha does not appear to play an important role.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Kassis, R.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Larrous, F.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Estaquier, J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bourhy, H.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["*Apoptosis", "Animals", "Apoptosis Regulatory Proteins", "Caspase 8", "Caspases/*metabolism", "HeLa Cells", "Humans", "Lyssavirus/*pathogenicity", "Membrane Glycoproteins/*metabolism", "Mice", "Neuroblastoma", "Receptors, Tumor Necrosis Factor/metabolism", "Signal Transduction", "TNF-Related Apoptosis-Inducing Ligand", "Tumor Cells, Cultured", "Tumor Necrosis Factor-alpha/*metabolism", "Viral Matrix Proteins/*metabolism", "Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/0e0c0178c783afda0c8060291fcae06e", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/6fa2639747843a07c7e5e6f94f06231c27949dcd64e3f874ec82dd4be596a157", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/R2H4N52N", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/R2H4N52N", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/55db2b140754e3cbc8fad79a42eb572c!/b231659-234219", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "re